  "essence": "Direct one-shot prediction with only terminal supervision fails on tasks that require multi-step, compositional reasoning because there are no explicit intermediate states to structure computation and assign credit.",
  "paraphrases": {
    "LLM_NLP": "LLMs optimized to emit a short final token sequence without intermediate reasoning tokens fail on multi-hop questions: over long context length, attention heads cannot maintain dependencies across many decoding steps, so perplexity can be low while final-answer accuracy degrades.",
    "MULTIMODAL": "Vision–language models that map image embeddings and text prompts directly to an answer without intermediate cross-modal grounding fail on compositional queries: query-conditioned attention over visual tokens drifts, cross-modal alignment errors accumulate, and VQA accuracy drops on multi-hop benchmarks.",
    "CV": "Single-shot perception that predicts final labels from dense feature maps fails on scenes requiring part–whole reasoning: at high spatial resolution, patch tokens lack persistent intermediates to propagate constraints across receptive fields, yielding fragmented segmentation masks and missed small objects.",
    "RL": "End-to-end policies trained with only terminal reward signals fail on long-horizon tasks: across extended rollouts the trajectory credit assignment is ambiguous, exploration collapses, and sample efficiency deteriorates even when a value baseline is present.",
    "IR_REC": "Retrieval pipelines that rely on a single query–document score per candidate without intermediate intent signals fail on multi-aspect queries: reranking with a cross-encoder over a large candidate pool sourced from an embedding index provides weak supervision, so recall@k and subtopic coverage degrade.",
    "SPEECH": "End-to-end ASR that maps spectrograms directly to transcripts without intermediate phoneme or alignment states fails on long-form or noisy speech: acoustic frame evidence cannot be consistently synchronized, increasing WER and instability under realistic conditions.",
    "ROBOTICS": "Reactive control that outputs actions directly in the sensorimotor loop without an explicit motion plan or contact reasoning fails on multi-step manipulation: compounding errors in the learned dynamics model over long horizons reduce task success and hinder sim-to-real transfer."
  }
}

